NEXT.JS REWRITES (next.config.js) — only if using proxy pattern
  ✅ Source: "/api/:path*"  →  Destination: "${BACKEND_URL}/api/:path*"
  ✅ This does NOT double the prefix — source and destination both have /api
  ❌ NEVER set source: "/api/:path*" → destination: "${BACKEND_URL}/:path*"
     (strips /api from backend, breaking all routes)
  ❌ NEVER use both rewrites AND a baseURL with /api — pick one pattern

ENV VARIABLES
  ✅ Frontend env: NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000  (no trailing slash)
  ✅ Backend env:  BACKEND_URL used only for next.config.js rewrites
  ✅ Vercel: set NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL to your Railway backend URL
  ❌ NEVER commit .env or .env.local to git

TYPESCRIPT
  ✅ Every API response typed with an interface matching the response shape contract above
  ✅ Always destructure with defaults: const { items = [], total = 0 } = data
  ✅ Optional chaining everywhere on API data: data?.items?.[0]?.player?.name
  ❌ NEVER trust API response shape — always default-initialize destructured values

