PART 7 — COMMON FUTURE ERROR SIGNATURES & THEIR CAUSES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ERROR                         → ROOT CAUSE                 → FIX
--------------------------------------------------------------------
GET /api/api/...  404         → baseURL includes /api       → Remove /api from baseURL
GET /api/health   404         → route defined as /health    → Add /api prefix to route
500 "column X not exist"      → Migration not run           → Run run_migrations.sql
500 "could not connect"       → asyncpg.connect() per req   → Use pool.acquire()
500 "MissingGreenlet"         → Sync SQLAlchemy in async    → Use select().where()
500 "Cannot connect to DB"    → Railway OOM restart         → Reduce worker count to 1
500 "module has no attribute" → Missing app.core.state      → Create core/state.py
500 "lazy loading forbidden"  → SQLAlchemy lazy relation    → Use selectinload()
CORS preflight blocked        → Wildcard + credentials      → Explicit allowed origins
Container OOM crash           → numpy/scipy top-level import→ Lazy import in function
Stale data (Feb 2026)         → Hardcoded date in mock      → Use datetime.now()
401 on Odds API               → Key exhausted, no fallback  → Add backup key failover
Deployment boot loop          → alembic before uvicorn fails→ Check migration syntax
PORT crash on Railway         → int(os.getenv("PORT","8000"))→ Use or 8000 pattern
Git push from app code        → subprocess.run(git...) call → Remove, never do this

